\v 1 \w A|strong="H3068"\w* little later \w Naomi|strong="H5281"\w* said \w to|strong="H1245"\w* Ruth, “\w My|strong="H1245"\w* \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w*, don't \w you|strong="H3808"\w* think \w I|strong="H3808"\w* \w should|strong="H1323"\w* \w find|strong="H1245"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* husband \w and|strong="H1323"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w good|strong="H3190"\w* home?\f + \fr 3:1 \ft “A husband and a good home”: the word used here refers to the rest and security provided from being married.\f*
\v 2 Don't ignore \w the|strong="H1961"\w* fact \w that|strong="H1931"\w* \w Boaz|strong="H1162"\w*, whose \w women|strong="H5291"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* worked \w with|strong="H1961"\w*, \w is|strong="H1931"\w* closely related \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w*. \w Now|strong="H6258"\w* \w tonight|strong="H3915"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* busy \w winnowing|strong="H2219"\w* grain \w on|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* \w threshing|strong="H1637"\w* \w floor|strong="H1637"\w*.\f + \fr 3:2 \ft Grain was processed first by threshing, a procedure by which the grain was separated from the stalks. Then it was winnowed by throwing it up in the air so that the wind would carry away the outer shell of the grain called chaff, and the grain would fall back down to be collected.\f*
